=Generate YouTube metadata for this video:

**Original Prompt:** {{ $json.original_prompt }}
**Video Description:** {{ $json.video_description }}

Create an engaging YouTube title (max 100 chars), detailed description (include keywords naturally), and relevant tags (comma-separated).

Return ONLY a JSON object with this exact structure:
{
  "youtube_title": "Your title here",
  "youtube_description": "Your description here",
  "youtube_tags": "tag1, tag2, tag3, tag4, tag5"
}

parameters.jsCode:
// Get binary video data
const binaryData = $input.first().binary?.data;

if (!binaryData) {
  throw new Error("No binary data found");
}

// Create data URL
const base64Video = binaryData.data;
const mimeType = binaryData.mimeType || 'video/mp4';
const dataUrl = `data:${mimeType};base64,${base64Video}`;

return {
  json: {
    videoUrl: dataUrl
  }
};
